1.**There is a per CLR/Process GC not in OS lvl.**

Basically Garbage Collector in.Net has two modes **Workstation** and **Server**.

**Workstation** modes assumes thath other applications are running on the machine and does not hog the cpu(**which means that other process could use cpu for their own  GC collection**),allow other applications /process uses cpu for **THEIR OWN** GC process.


**Server** mode assumes that there is no other  application running on the server and it assumes that all cpu on the machine are available to assist with completing GC.This GC mode caused managed heap to be splited in a couple of sections  on per CPU.And as you can guess each cpu is responsible for each section of managed heap.

By default all applications in .Net(including ASP.NET) running on the Workstation mod but we can enable through config file Server mod.Like this

    &lt;configuration&gt;
      &lt;runtime&gt;
       &lt;gcServer enabled = &quot;true&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/runtime&gt;
     &lt;/configuration&gt;


 2. OutOfMemory exception will be thrown when GC will go throug all **zero** based generations objects and figured out that there is not enough memeory. And start making collection through all generations **one and two**. If in that case it determines that there is again not enoguh memory will be thrown OutOfMemoryException.

Your query returns only 1 row because of the condition:

    WHERE Name=&#39;Ram&#39;

So you will always get 1 as result.&lt;br/&gt;

Select the row number from the subquery with [`RANK()`][1] to handle ties for salaries and use `DESC` to sort descending the salaries: 

    SELECT t.RowNum FROM (
      SELECT Name, RANK() OVER (ORDER BY Salary DESC) RowNum
      FROM Employee
    ) t
    WHERE t.Name=&#39;Ram&#39;;
Another simpler and maybe more efficient solution without window functions:

    SELECT COUNT(*) + 1 RowNum
    FROM Employee 
    WHERE Salary &gt; (SELECT Salary FROM Employee WHERE Name=&#39;Ram&#39;);


  [1]: https://www.sqlite.org/windowfunctions.html

