answers.body_markdown:
When your bot receives an event of type message, it invokes your callback and inside your callback you only receive `message`, so of course `command` will be undefined. Looking through some examples, I believe it should be like this:
```
const args = message.content.slice(config.prefix.length).trim().split(/ +/g);
const command = args.shift().toLowerCase();
```
[Here](https://gist.github.com/eslachance/3349734a98d30011bb202f47342601d3) is the full example, I suggest checking it out.

